## Integration tests (`crates/server/tests/workers_integration.rs`)

All task-queue tests use **`WORKERS_DB_TEST_MUTEX`** with **`reset_worker_tables`** to avoid cross-binary Postgres races with other integration binaries when CI uses `--test-threads=1`.

Tests (require `DATABASE_URL`):

1. **`pull_reclaims_stale_worker_job_then_assigns_to_fresh_worker`** — stale `w-stale` holds assigned job; `w-fresh` pull gets it; `reclaim_count == 1`, `worker_id == w-fresh`.
2. **`pull_fails_job_when_reclaim_count_at_cap_for_stale_worker`** — `reclaim_count == 3`, max 3; pull fails job with `[MAX_WORKER_LOSS_RETRIES]`; puller gets 204.
3. **`pull_lease_expires_long_running_assigned_job`** — `job_lease_seconds = 1`, `assigned_at` 10 minutes ago; `[JOB_LEASE_EXPIRED]`; worker still “fresh” (stale threshold 3600s) so lease path is isolated.
4. **`pull_idempotent_and_complete_releases_job`** — two pulls same `job_id`; complete success; third pull 204.
5. **`stale_worker_cannot_pull`** — 409 `worker_stale`.

Also: **`workers_endpoints_require_auth`** extended with pull and complete paths.

